						<div class="postbody">I'd be willing to invest some effort in creating a shared universe for NESdev.<br /><br />A fairy tale crossover world like that of <em>Shrek</em> or <em>Fables</em> or <em>Once Upon a Time</em> or <em>RWBY</em> or <em>Cheshire Crossing</em> would be a starting point because the original <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grimms%27_Fairy_Tales" class="postlink">Grimm</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histoires_ou_contes_du_temps_pass%C3%A9" class="postlink">Perrault</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Lang's_Fairy_Books" class="postlink">Lang</a>/<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hans_Christian_Andersen" class="postlink">Andersen</a> versions of the characters are public domain. (Hence why Sachen didn't have to pay anyone for <em>Little Red Hood</em>.) Even a talking donkey is PD if his characterization doesn't resemble Eddie Murphy, as talking donkeys form part of the plot of Collodi's <em>The Adventures of Pinocchio</em>. I've suggested doing fairy tale world before, particularly in discussions about &quot;Let's make a fighting game&quot;, but I seem to remember others saying it'd still be too much work.</div>

