					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If the mod/rom hack was called &quot;Briefcase Creatures&quot; or admittedly something more catchy, then Nintendo would not have cared.<br /><br />As soon as you try to introduce to the public a creative work using an active trademark belonging to another company without authorization, you're going to get legal action taken.<br /><br />Nintendo has to take legal action to say that Pokemon(tm) Prism is not an authorized work and cannot use the word &quot;Pokemon&quot;.<br />Nintendo has to take legal action to say that the author does not have permission to use the stylized Logo related to Pokemon.<br /><br />The sky is not falling.<br /><br />In the law you HAVE to take action no matter how big or small.<br />Because let's say there's an egregious blatant misuse of the Pokemon logo on some toy. The lawyers representing that toy company can point out, hey... uh... why didn't you take legal action against this or that or these other things? Hmmm??? And so it goes.</div>

